===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|melten}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|meltan||to consume by fire, melt, burn up; dissolve, digest}} and {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|mieltan||to melt; digest; refine, purge; exhaust}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*meltaną||to dissolve, melt}} and {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*maltijaną||to dissolve, melt}}, both from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*(s)mel-||to beat, crush, grind}}. Cognate with {{etyl|is|-}} {{m|is|melta||to melt, digest}}.

