===Verb===
{{en-verb|melts|melting|melted|past2=molt|past2_qual=rare|melted|past_ptc2=molten}}

# {{label|en|ergative}} To change (or to be changed) from a solid state to a liquid state, usually by a gradual heat.
#: ''I '''melted''' butter to make a cake.''
#: ''When the weather is warm, the snowman will disappear; he will '''melt'''.''
# {{label|en|intransitive|figuratively}} To [[dissolve]], [[disperse]], [[vanish]].
#: ''His troubles '''melted''' away.''
# {{label|en|transitive|figurative}} To [[soften]], as by a warming or kindly influence; to relax; to render gentle or susceptible to mild influences; sometimes, in a bad sense, to take away the firmness of; to weaken.
#* Shakespeare
#*: Thou would'st have {{...}} '''melted''' down thy youth.
#* Dryden
#*: For pity '''melts''' the mind to love.
# {{label|en|intransitive|colloquial}} To be very hot and [[sweat]] [[profuse]]ly.
#: ''Help me! I'm '''melting'''!''

